<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Don't listen to Brinlayl.  <p>

Wizards do get better but after lvl 20.  So hang in there, have patience and you will see the incredible amounts of damage wizards can do in a short time.  <br>
Magicians are equal to Wizards but get a huge experience hit from the pets.  Yes, pets steal exp, and alot of it.  That's the price to pay for a bodyguard and the cost of components to make a pet.  It takes alot longer to lvl with a magician.  <p>

I played both and wizard was my final choice.  It was just too much hastle with pets since they like to run off in dugeons and bring back trains just for you.<p>

Warriors can solo maybe until lvl 20 but that's when they start screaming for a casters help.  <p>

Feel free to examine other classes to find one that best suits your needs.  <br>
Have patience with a wizard, it will certainly pay off.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
